PointFinder turns small pathfinders games into big digitally powered adventures. Check in at real-world bases and solve challenges.
---
This is the companion app for PointFinder, a platform that digitally poweres pathfinder missions and outdoor challenge games.
Whether you are a player in the field or an operator running the event, PointFinder connects teams, bases, and progress in real time.

For players:
Join a game with a QR code or join code
Explore base locations on the map
Check in at physical bases using NFC
Unlock and solve text or photo challenges
Keep playing offline and sync actions when connection returns
Track progress by base status from not visited to completed

For operators:
Sign in and access your games or coolaborate with on other's games.
Monitor teams and base activity on a live map
View base-by-base team progress and submission states
Write and link NFC tags to bases from iPhone

Built for real-world events:
Designed for pathfinder organizations, camps, and mission activities
Multi-language support: English, Portuguese, and German
Push notifications and resilient sync flows for active games

Important:
A game code from your organizer is required to join as a player.
An operator account is required to use operator tools.
NFC features require a compatible iPhone.
Location access is used during active missions for map and team tracking.
Photo submissions require an internet connection.
